- `MultiLabelClassificationTask` — specialises
  `SequenceClassificationTask` for multi-label classification, where
  multiple labels can be simultaneously active for a single input.
  *Ex: a support ticket tagged simultaneously as "billing",
  "technical_issue", and "urgent".*
  Unlike single-label classification (softmax, scores sum to 1),
  multi-label classification applies a sigmoid per label — each score
  is independent and represents the probability of that label being
  active.
  - `threshold: float` — decision threshold above which a label is
    considered active; applied in `predict()` over the scores
    returned by `predict_proba()`.
  - `predict(text) List[str]` — overrides parent; returns all labels
    whose score exceeds `self.threshold`.
  - `predict_proba(text) Dict[str, float]` — overrides parent;
    returns independent activation scores per label (sigmoid outputs,
    not a probability distribution).
